reviews.text: Small local restaurant with limited seats. A little bit expensive but worth the money.

Horrible place to go to. I was planning to go somewhere other than Starbucks so I found this place. The location is fine behind sheung wan civic centre. Food is overpriced and portions are small. I went with a friend and they sent us upstairs due to no available spots on first floor. 

My friend and I ordered a coffee and iced chocolate for afternoon tea also a spaghetti. The coffee wasn't hot it was just warm (no repelling of hand when touching the cup side)  and the iced chocolate hk$68 has horrible taste extremely bitter. It was so bad I had one sip and left it. 

I would not recommend going here however the taste of the food was fine. I ordered the spaghetti hk$148.

Food: 7/10
Price: bad 
Drinks: poor
Food is okay at a higher price.  I didn't try coffee.  Looks good.

The atmosphere is relaxing and cozy. The food and drink are tasty and can see the afford from the chief and barista. It will be better if they can decorate the alley next to them. Although it gives me raw and local vibe, it looks miserable when they open the side door for ventilation purpose at the same time.

Not too many choice for breakfast menu and very limited space and limited seats. Pastry and muffin options are available for breakfast option at reasonable price but the size is smallest I have ever seen. 
Food is ok. Americano is ok. Service is ok. Nothing much to draw me back for revisit when there are so many similar shops near by .

reviews.text: 很多台灣小吃，刈包、甜不辣、香腸、肉燥飯...ok...但份量有點少。Very friendly like in Taiwan.

要了個外表漂漂亮亮的Raspberry Tartlet w/ Pink Meringue $48

撻底是淋的質地, 但Tartlet不應該是硬脆的嗎? Raspberry 係內裡一層果醬之類的醬, 加上面頭甜甜的"馬令"! 理論上是可行的但手藝所限, 做不出應有的效果, 只得個賣相! ! 反而同場購入的台灣咖啡荳(似乎是得獎的拼配荳) $130/半磅, 飲落又幾順喉, 雖是中度烘焙但香氣非常, 有回甘, 值得推介, 唯一一點是這荳包裝上出了問題, 包裝袋撕去第一下之後剩餘紙口太短無法用手腳底袋口拉開, 最終要用剪刀剪開, 這問題後來跟台灣生產商反映, 他們說往後跟進改善, 希望如果下次再幫襯時是新一批荳吧!
